    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "17352e40_7b5619a5",
        "filename": "util/file/file_io_posix.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-28T20:03:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "May also be EOPNOTSUPP if the filesystem doesn’t handle O_TMPFILE but the kernel understands it. The man page also says that EISDIR and ENOENT need to be checked to determine whether the kernel provides O_TMPFILE support, which is seemingly what you’re using EINVAL for. I think you’ll need to look at a pre-O_TMPFILE kernel to figure this out, in addition to glibc to see if it does anything like remap errors.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 164,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 164,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "cb2e1ef13f5704284b49e3b90b84ac5e4eb4f56f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cc7e297d_a17b797c",
        "filename": "util/file/file_io_posix.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 171,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-28T20:03:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since you’re looking at this as a FileHandle and not just an int fd, use kInvalidFileHandle. But read the next comment first.",
      "revId": "cb2e1ef13f5704284b49e3b90b84ac5e4eb4f56f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a4c6c0a4_0d4a2a68",
        "filename": "util/file/file_io_posix.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 173,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-28T20:03:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What’s the point of using a base::FilePath for this when you just want to get the const char* out of the underlying std::string anyway? Why not just use the std::string from the start, and save a pair of .value() calls?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 173,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 173,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "cb2e1ef13f5704284b49e3b90b84ac5e4eb4f56f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "62e6bb21_cfc5396d",
        "filename": "util/file/file_io_posix.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 174,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-28T20:03:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is what we have RandomString() for, instead of UUID.\n\nYou can do %s.%d.%s and put getpid() in the middle. Doesn’t get you additional randomness, but avoids innocent collisions and, most importantly, provides attribution to the process in case the unlink() fails.",
      "revId": "cb2e1ef13f5704284b49e3b90b84ac5e4eb4f56f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
